INSERT INTO cars VALUES(132,'Volkswagen','Touareg','Touareg 1 (7L)',2004,NULL,'00s','SUV','Germany',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-05 00:00:00','adventure',NULL,'3.0 TDI V6');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(133,'Volkswagen','Touareg','Touareg 2 (7P)',2011,NULL,'10s','SUV','Germany',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-05 00:00:00','adventure',NULL,'3.0 TDI V6');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(134,'Volkswagen','Touareg','Touareg 3 (CR)',2019,NULL,'10s','SUV','Germany',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-05 00:00:00','adventure',NULL,'3.0 TDI V6');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(135,'Mercedes-Benz','300 SL','W198',1954,1957,'classic','coupe','Germany',1400,'The car that started it all. Born from Mercedes'' dominant 1952 Carrera Panamericana racer, the 300 SL Gullwing was the world''s fastest production car at launch. Its Bosch mechanical direct fuel injection was a first for any production car. The tubular spaceframe necessitated those iconic doors ? you didn''t choose gullwings for style, you got them because the sills were too high for conventional doors. Max Hoffman convinced Mercedes to build 1,000 for the US market. They built 1,400. Every one is now worth seven figures.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','hyper','SL','Gullwing');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(136,'Mercedes-Benz','190 SL','W121',1955,1963,'classic','roadster','Germany',25881,'The people''s SL. Where the 300 SL was an exotic racer for the road, the 190 SL was a beautiful touring roadster you could actually afford. Shared the Gullwing''s styling DNA and independent suspension but used a shortened W121 sedan floorpan instead of a spaceframe. The 1.9L SOHC four was essentially a 300 SL inline-six with two cylinders lopped off, fed by twin Solex carburetors. Not fast ? 104 HP pushed 1,160 kg to 60 in 13.3 seconds ? but gorgeous and usable. Grace Kelly drove one. That''s all you need to know.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','classic','SL','190 SL');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(137,'Mercedes-Benz','280 SL','W113',1967,1971,'classic','roadster','Germany',23887,'The Pagoda. Named for its concave hardtop roof that mimics a Japanese temple. Paul Bracq''s design is arguably the most beautiful SL ever ? certainly the most elegant. Underneath, Bela Barenyi''s safety innovations: crumple zones, rigid passenger cell, all-wheel independent suspension. The 2.8L M130 inline-six with Bosch fuel injection produced 168 HP and made the 280 SL a genuine 124 mph car. Drum brakes gave way to discs. The interior was a paragon of teutonic restraint. Values have tripled in the last decade ? the market finally caught up to what enthusiasts always knew.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','classic','SL','Pagoda');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(138,'Mercedes-Benz','560 SL','R107',1986,1989,'80s','roadster','Germany',49347,'The Panzerwagen. The R107 ran for 18 years (1971-1989) ? the longest SL production run ever. The 560 SL was the final, most powerful variant, sold only in North America and Australia. The 5.5L M117 V8 made 227 HP and sounded magnificent doing it. At 1,680 kg it was no sports car, but it didn''t need to be ? this was a personal luxury cruiser with the build quality of a vault. The R107 outlived its intended replacement twice. Miami Vice drove one. So did half of Beverly Hills. The definition of 1980s automotive glamour.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','classic','SL','560 SL');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(139,'Mercedes-Benz','500 SL','R129',1990,1998,'90s','roadster','Germany',79827,'The R129 brought the SL into the modern era. The M119 5.0L DOHC 32-valve V8 was a masterpiece ? 315 HP in US trim, smooth as butter and happy to rev. The body was designed to survive a crash with a moose (yes, that was an actual design requirement). The automatic roll bar deployed in 0.3 seconds if the car sensed a rollover. Princess Diana drove one ? without security ? which caused a minor scandal and a spike in SL sales. The pre-1996 cars suffer from Mercedes'' infamous biodegradable wiring harness (bean counter decision, not an engineering one). Incredible value today for what you get.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','luxury','SL','500 SL');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(140,'Mercedes-Benz','SL 600','R129',1993,2001,'90s','roadster','Germany',11089,'The R129 V12 flagship. The M120 6.0L V12 is the same engine Pagani would later use in the Zonda ? that''s how good it is. 389 HP, 570 Nm of torque, and turbine-smooth refinement. The SL 600 came standard with ADS active suspension, a feature that was optional (and rare) on the V8 cars. Only 11,089 were built over 9 years ? Mercedes averaged barely 1,200 per year. The problem? When something breaks, everything is twice as expensive because there are two of everything ? coil packs, fuel pumps, and 24 spark plugs buried under the intake manifold. The pre-1996 biodegradable wiring harness makes it worse. A car for masochists with taste.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','luxury','SL','SL 600');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(141,'Mercedes-AMG','SL55 AMG','R230',2002,2008,'00s','roadster','Germany',NULL,'The R230 SL55 AMG was the car that made AMG a household name. Under the hood sat the M113K ? a 5.4L SOHC 24-valve V8 with a Lysholm screw-type supercharger cramming 11.6 psi of boost. 493 HP and an earth-moving 700 Nm of torque from just 2,750 RPM. Car and Driver tested 0-60 in 3.6 seconds with rollout ? supercar territory in 2003. The retractable hardtop (Vario Roof) transformed it from open cruiser to sealed GT in 16 seconds. ABC active suspension and SBC brake-by-wire were cutting edge but now expensive to maintain. The SL55 defined the modern AMG formula: massive torque, glorious supercharger whine, and a presence that makes valets park it up front. Depreciation has made them the cheapest 500 HP car you can buy.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','hot','SL','SL55 AMG');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(142,'Mercedes-AMG','SL63 AMG','R231',2013,2020,'10s','roadster','Germany',NULL,'The R231 SL63 traded the old supercharger for twin turbos and gained the M157 ? AMG''s 5.5L biturbo V8. In facelift form (2016-2020), it made 577 HP and a crushing 900 Nm of torque. The entire body went aluminum, shedding weight from the porky R230. The MCT multi-clutch transmission (no torque converter) gave sharper shifts. But the R231 was caught in an awkward place ? too heavy to be a true sports car, too focused to be a pure grand tourer, and launching into a world that increasingly wanted SUVs. Sales were modest. The R231 may be the most undervalued AMG of the modern era ? 577 HP, hand-built engine, and prices that have bottomed out.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','hot','SL','SL63 AMG');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(143,'Mercedes-AMG','SL 63','R232',2022,NULL,'modern','roadster','Germany',NULL,'The R232 marks a fundamental shift ? for the first time, the SL is developed entirely by AMG, not Mercedes-Benz. The 4.0L M177 biturbo V8 (hot-vee layout, turbos inside the V) produces 577 HP and 800 Nm. For the first time in SL history, there''s all-wheel drive (4MATIC+). The retractable hardtop was dropped in favor of a fabric soft top ? saving weight and reclaiming trunk space. 0-60 in 3.0 seconds. Rear-axle steering. Active aero. The interior has HyperScreens and ambient lighting that responds to your driving mode. It''s the fastest, most capable SL ever built. Whether it''s the most soulful is a different question. At ,000, it better be.','[]','2026-06-04 23:16:46','hot','SL','SL 63 4MATIC+');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(144,'Mercedes-Benz','C-Class','W204',2007,2014,'00s','sedan','Germany',2400000,'The third-generation C-Class (W204) is widely considered the "sweet spot" of the lineage 窶・a clean, Bauhaus-influenced restyle by Murat G\u00fcnak that won unanimous praise for finally making the C look as grown-up as the E. Built on the new W204 platform with a longer wheelbase, the car finally had presence in its segment. The US-market C300 used the M272 3.0L V6 (228 hp) mated to a 7G-Tronic (722.9) automatic. European buyers had the M271 1.8L turbo I4 and the M276 3.5L V6. The facelift in 2011 introduced the new Mercedes corporate face (single-louvre grille, LED-styled headlights) and the M271 EVO engines. Mechanically robust but not without foibles: the M271 balance shaft gear (2008-2010), the M272 balance shaft wear (a well-known Mercedes mid-2000s V6 issue), and 7G-Tronic mechatronic sleeve failures. With maintenance, these run 250K+ miles. The C63 AMG variant with the M156 6.2L V8 is the obvious collector car, but the ordinary C300 is the value play.','[]','2026-06-08 12:00:00','warm','C-Class','C300');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(145,'Mercedes-Benz','C-Class','W205',2014,2021,'10s','sedan','Germany',2500000,'The fourth-generation C-Class (W205) is the car that made the C-Class feel like a baby S-Class. Launched in 2014 on a heavily reworked W204 platform, the W205 shed ~100 kg versus its predecessor and introduced a modular interior architecture shared with the E and S. The US C300 uses the M274 2.0L turbocharged inline-four (241 hp, 273 lb-ft) paired with the 7G-Tronic Plus or, from 2015, the new 9G-Tronic (725.0) 窶・a nine-speed that finally solved the harsh shifting of the older seven-speed. The 2018 facelift added the M264 engine family and the new corporate grille. C300s equipped with AIRMATIC air suspension are delightful on the road but a $1,500-2,500 per-corner repair waiting to happen. The W205 is mechanically far more reliable than the W204; the M274 balance shaft issue (early 2015-2016) is the most well-known weakness. MBUX arrived in 2019, replacing COMAND. A post-facelift C300 is a near-luxury benchmark for the segment.','[]','2026-06-08 12:00:00','warm','C-Class','C300');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(146,'Mercedes-Benz','GLK-Class','X204',2008,2015,'00s','SUV','Germany',530000,'The X204 GLK is the squared-off, upright compact SUV Mercedes built to take on the BMW X3 and Audi Q5. Designed during the period when Mercedes still believed an SUV should look like a Gel\u00e4ndewagen, the GLK is a styling anti-thesis to the curvy modern crossovers 窶・and that is precisely why a cult following developed. The GLK350 uses the M272 3.5L V6 (268 hp) mated to the 7G-Tronic (722.9) and 4MATIC AWD. Diesel GLK250 Bluetec (OM651 2.1L I4) was a hit in Europe; never officially sold in the US. The 2013 facelift brought the new corporate face and the M276 3.5L V6. Mechanically it shares most of its drivetrain with the W204 C-Class, including the M272 balance shaft weakness and 7G-Tronic mechatronic sleeve issues. Lower control arm bushings and ball joints wear out around 80-100K miles. Sunroof track and electrical gremlins are common. The 2013+ facelift is the one to buy 窶・quieter, more refined, fewer electrical issues. The GLK was replaced by the GLC (X253) in 2015.','[]','2026-06-08 12:00:00','warm','GLK','GLK350');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(147,'Mercedes-Benz','C-Class','W205',2015,2018,'10s','sedan','Germany',NULL,'The W205 C 400 4MATIC was Mercedes'' answer to the BMW 340i xDrive and Audi S4 窶・a sweet-spot sedan slotting between the 4-cyl C300 and the AMG C43. Under the hood sits the M276 DE 30 AL 窶・a 3.0L biturbo V6 producing 329 hp and 354 lb-ft (480 Nm) of torque from just 1,600 rpm. The same basic V6 architecture that would later be re-engineered into the AMG M276 (C43) and the straight-six M256 (E450). The C 400 came only with 4MATIC AWD and the 7G-Tronic Plus (722.9 variant). Discontinued after 2018 to make room for the C43 AMG, which shares the same engine with a 33-hp bump and AMG-specific hardware. The C 400 is the under-the-radar pick: nearly all the AMG C43''s character at a ~$5-8K lower price on the used market, and without the AMG-specific air suspension or running gear to maintain. The known weakness is the M276 balance shaft wear (less severe than the M272 but still a real concern on early cars) and the 7G-Tronic mechatronic. Buy a 2017+ with service records showing transmission fluid changes.','[]','2026-06-08 13:00:00','warm','C-Class','C 400');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(148,'Mercedes-Benz','C-Class','W205',2016,2018,'10s','sedan','Germany',NULL,'The C 450 AMG 4MATIC is one of the most interesting cars Mercedes made in the W205 era. Born from the short-lived "AMG Sport" badge (2015-2017) that sat between the standard C300 and the full-fat AMG C43/C63, the C 450 used the M276 3.0L biturbo V6 tuned to 362 hp and 384 lb-ft (520 Nm) 窶・essentially identical output to the C43 AMG that succeeded it. The key difference: AMG-specific dampers and a sport exhaust, but no AMG engine build, no AMG-specific air suspension, no AMG seats. When Mercedes consolidated the lineup in 2016, the C 450 was absorbed into the AMG C 43 and the badge disappeared. The C 450 AMG is the dark-horse performance value: nearly all the C43 character without the AMG tax on used prices, and with a less-stressed engine (no AMG power runup). 0-60 in 4.6 seconds. The 9G-Tronic (725.0) is a real upgrade over the 7G-Tronic in the C 400. Production was brief: roughly 2016-2018. The only meaningful failure modes are the M276 balance shaft (mild) and 9G-Tronic mechatronic plate (cheap fix).','[]','2026-06-08 13:00:00','hot','C-Class','C 450 AMG');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(149,'Mercedes-Benz','E-Class','W213',2020,2023,'modern','sedan','Germany',NULL,'The E 450 4MATIC is the cleanest expression of Mercedes'' modular inline-six engine family. The M256 3.0L inline-six uses a hot-V twin-scroll turbo layout (turbos nestled inside the V between cylinder banks) and a 48-volt mild-hybrid system (EQ Boost) that adds 21 hp and 184 lb-ft briefly under hard acceleration and smooths the start/stop function. Output: 362 hp and 369 lb-ft (500 Nm) of torque. Paired with the 9G-Tronic (725.0). Available only with 4MATIC in the US. The W213 LCI (facelift, sold as the 2020 model in the US, 2018-2019 in Europe) brought a revised exterior, the new steering wheel, the latest MBUX infotainment, and 窶・most importantly 窶・the inline-six M256 that replaced the aging M276 V6. The 48V mild-hybrid system was cutting-edge when new and the source of much of the early W213 reliability concern: the ISG (integrated starter-generator) and 48V battery on 2020-2021 E450s had a meaningful failure rate (warranty-covered, but expensive out of warranty). By 2022 the issues were largely engineered out. The E 450 is the modern E-Class in its most-balanced form 窶・the I6 smoothness is a real step up from any V6 Mercedes has made, and the fuel economy is genuinely impressive for the performance (24 mpg combined).','[]','2026-06-08 13:00:00','warm','E-Class','E 450 4MATIC');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(150,'BMW','5 Series','G30 LCI',2021,2023,'modern','sedan','Germany',NULL,'The G30 LCI 540i xDrive is the facelifted version of the G30 5 Series, sold in the US from 2021-2023. Same B58 3.0L twin-turbo I6 (the US 540i kept the non-hybrid B58; Euro G30 LCI got the 48V B58 mild hybrid that we do not get), same ZF 8HP automatic, same xDrive AWD. The LCI brought revised exterior styling (larger kidney grille), iDrive 7/8 infotainment, and a more refined interior. Critically, the post-LCI B58 has the valve cover gasket and VANOS issues largely engineered out, making it one of the most reliable modern BMW engines. The 540i is the volume seller in the G30 lineup and the direct competitor to the Mercedes E 450 W213 LCI. Lower used prices than the E 450 ($28-42K vs $35-55K) reflect a combination of slightly older platform, higher volume production, and BMW''s traditionally weaker residual values.','[]','2026-06-08 14:00:00','warm','5 Series','540i xDrive');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(151,'Genesis','G80','1st gen (DH)',2017,2020,'10s','sedan','South Korea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-08 18:09:12','sleeper','Lambda II','G80 3.3T Sport');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(152,'Genesis','G70','1st gen (facelift)',2022,NULL,'modern','sedan','South Korea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-08 18:09:12','sharp','Smartstream/Theta III','G70 2.5T');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(153,'Genesis','GV70','1st gen',2022,NULL,'modern','SUV','South Korea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-08 18:09:12','versatile','Smartstream/Theta III','GV70 2.5T');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(154,'Genesis','GV80','1st gen',2020,NULL,'modern','SUV','South Korea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-08 18:09:12','premium','Smartstream/Lambda III','GV80 3.5T');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(155,'Audi','A6','C7',2012,2018,'10s','sedan','Germany',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-06-08 18:09:12','refined','EA837','3.0T quattro');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(156,'Volvo','S60','3rd gen (SPA)',2019,NULL,'10s','sedan','Sweden',NULL,'The SPA-platform S60 T5 is the base-tier Geely-era Volvo sedan. Powered by the VEA B4204T26 2.0L turbo I4 producing 250 hp, mated to the Aisin TG-81SC 8-speed automatic. FWD standard, EPA 23/34 mpg. This is the "smart" Volvo 窶・all the safety and Scandinavian design without the supercharger complexity. The T5 is the reliability sweet spot of the VEA family: simpler, fewer failure modes, nearly as fast as the T6 in daily driving. 2019+ SPA models are generally sorted after early VEA oil consumption issues were resolved.',NULL,'2026-06-08 18:22:50','understated','VEA/Drive-E','S60 T5');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(157,'Volvo','S60','3rd gen (SPA)',2019,2021,'10s','sedan','Sweden',NULL,'The S60 T6 adds an Eaton Roots-type supercharger to the VEA 2.0L turbo I4, producing 316 hp and 295 lb-ft. The supercharger operates via electromagnetic clutch from idle to ~3,500 rpm, then hands off to the BorgWarner turbo. AWD standard. EPA 21/32 mpg. The T6 is the "enthusiast" Volvo 窶・instant low-end torque from the supercharger, linear power delivery, genuinely quick. But the supercharger clutch is a known failure point ($2-3.5K), and oil consumption issues are more common on T6s. 2019+ models are improved over early 2015-2016 VEA engines.',NULL,'2026-06-08 18:22:50','sleeper','VEA/Drive-E','S60 T6 AWD');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(158,'Volvo','XC60','2nd gen (SPA)',2018,NULL,'10s','SUV','Sweden',NULL,'The SPA-platform XC60 T5 is the volume-seller Volvo SUV. Same VEA B4204T23 2.0L turbo I4 (250 hp) as the S60 T5, but in a compact luxury SUV. FWD standard, AWD optional. EPA 22/29 mpg (FWD). The XC60 is consistently one of the highest-rated luxury compact SUVs 窶・Scandinavian design, class-leading safety, and the T5 is the reliability pick over the T6. Curb weight ~3,950 lbs. The 2018+ SPA platform is well-sorted.',NULL,'2026-06-08 18:22:50','practical','VEA/Drive-E','XC60 T5');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(159,'Volvo','XC60','2nd gen (SPA)',2018,2020,'10s','SUV','Sweden',NULL,'The XC60 T6 pairs the VEA turbo+supercharged B4204T27 (316 hp) with AWD. Same twincharged architecture as the S60 T6, but in a heavier SUV package (~4,045 lbs). EPA 20/27 mpg. The T6 is the "fast" XC60 窶・genuinely quick for a compact SUV, with instant supercharger response. Same trade-off: more power, more complexity, supercharger clutch risk. Discontinued after 2020 when Volvo shifted to B6 mild-hybrid variants.',NULL,'2026-06-08 18:22:50','performance-suv','VEA/Drive-E','XC60 T6 AWD');
INSERT INTO cars VALUES(160,'Volvo','S90','1st gen (SPA)',2017,2021,'10s','sedan','Sweden',NULL,'The S90 T6 is Volvos flagship sedan. Same B4204T27 turbo+supercharged 2.0L (316 hp) as the S60/XC60 T6, but in a larger, heavier package (4,819 lbs). AWD standard, EPA 21/31 mpg. The S90 is the "executive" Volvo 窶・gorgeous Scandinavian interior, Pilot Assist semi-autonomous driving, and genuinely premium feel. The 2017-2019 models had more early VEA issues; 2020+ is the sweet spot. MSRP started at $50,550 but massive depreciation means used examples are $20-35K.',NULL,'2026-06-08 18:22:50','executive','VEA/Drive-E','S90 T6 AWD');
