w dedicated luxury platform, but long-term data is thin and brand reliability is trending down.", "Audi/VW 48V mild hybrid systems are a documented reliability risk; failures as early as 50k km.", "The Lexus LS430 is the only car that matches the Subaru''s philosophy: overbuild, under-promise, last forever.", "Jaguar XJ X351: beautiful engineering but a financial trap; budget $2k/year maintenance and expect electrical gremlins.", "For a non-buyer enthusiast: studying E90, CLAR, M3, and Alpha platforms provides the best intellectual return on zero investment."], "comparison_groups": ["Luxury Sport Sedans (mid-size, 2015-2025): CT5-V vs 540i vs G80 3.5T vs A6 vs E-Class", "Flagships (full-size, 2000-2025): LS430/460 vs 7-series vs S-class vs A8 vs G90 vs XJ", "Used Market Bang-for-Buck (2017-2024): 540i G30 vs G80 3.5T vs Stinger vs Q50 Red Sport vs Lexus GS350", "Reliability Tiers (2010-2026): Lexus/Acura (best), BMW B58/Cadillac Alpha (good), Audi/VW (moderate), Jaguar/Porsche (risk/reward)"]}}], "count": 1}','success',NULL,1,'2026-05-30 23:27:43.937683');
